what is fastapi ?
Ans. FastAPI is a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for
building APIs with Python 3.6+ based on standard Python type hints
what is uvicorn ?
Ans. For the server that loads and serves your application.


The @app.get("/") tells FastAPI that the function right below
is in charge of handling requests that go to:
the path /
using a get operation

JSON stands for JavaScript Object Notation
JSON is a lightweight format for storing and transporting data
JSON is often used when data is sent from a server to a web page
JSON is "self-describing" and easy to understand